title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\SubnetworkLogConfig
name: SubnetworkLogConfig
description:
The available logging options for this subnetwork.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.SubnetworkLogConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.aggregation_interval
params.description: Can only be specified if VPC flow logging for this subnetwork is enabled. Toggles the aggregation interval for collecting flow logs. Increasing the interval time will reduce the amount of generated flow logs for long lasting connections. Default is an interval of 5 seconds per connection.

params.name: data.enable
params.description: Whether to enable flow logging for this subnetwork. If this field is not explicitly set, it will not appear in get listings. If not set the default behavior is to disable flow logging.

params.name: data.filter_expr
params.description: Can only be specified if VPC flow logs for this subnetwork is enabled. Export filter used to define which VPC flow logs should be logged.

params.name: data.flow_sampling
params.description: Can only be specified if VPC flow logging for this subnetwork is enabled. The value of the field must be in [0, 1]. Set the sampling rate of VPC flow logs within the subnetwork where 1.0 means all collected logs are reported and 0.0 means no logs are reported. Default is 0.5, which means half of all collected logs are reported.

params.name: data.metadata
params.description: Can only be specified if VPC flow logs for this subnetwork is enabled. Configures whether all, none or a subset of metadata fields should be added to the reported VPC flow logs. Default is INCLUDE_ALL_METADATA.

params.name: data.metadata_fields
params.description: Can only be specified if VPC flow logs for this subnetwork is enabled and "metadata" was set to CUSTOM_METADATA.
